sequenceDiagram
    participant P as Publisher
    participant B as EventBus
    participant MW as Middleware Chain
    participant TS as Type Subscribers
    participant AS as All Subscribers
    participant F as Filter
    participant CH as Subscriber Channel

    P->>B: Publish(event)
    activate B

    Note over B: Acquire RLock, check closed,<br/>copy middleware + subscriber slices,<br/>release RLock

    B->>MW: Apply middleware[0](event)
    MW-->>B: transformed event (or nil)

    alt Middleware returns nil
        Note over B: Event dropped,<br/>no delivery
    else Middleware returns event
        B->>MW: Apply middleware[1](event)
        MW-->>B: transformed event
        Note over B: ... repeat for all middleware ...
    end

    Note over B: atomic increment EventsPublished

    loop For each type-specific subscriber
        B->>F: subscriber.filter(event)
        alt Filter returns true (or no filter)
            F-->>B: true
            B->>CH: trySend(event, timeout)
            alt Channel has capacity
                CH-->>B: success
                Note over B: atomic increment EventsDelivered
            else Channel full / timeout
                CH-->>B: failure
                Note over B: atomic increment EventsDropped
            end
        else Filter returns false
            F-->>B: false
            Note over B: Skip this subscriber
        end
    end

    loop For each global (subscribe-all) subscriber
        B->>F: subscriber.filter(event)
        alt Filter passes
            F-->>B: true
            B->>CH: trySend(event, timeout)
            CH-->>B: success or failure
        else Filter rejects
            F-->>B: false
        end
    end

    deactivate B

    Note over CH: Subscriber reads from channel<br/>via select or range loop

    participant S as Subscriber
    CH->>S: <-sub.Channel
